This custom of the Germans formed a contrast to the Roman practice. Martial (vi. 7) complains that in spite of the Julian law, Telesina had married ten husbands in thirty days. With them the facilities for divorce seem to have nearly rivalled those amongst the Jews3 with whom a woman might be divorced for spoiling her husband's soup.
